Su Zhu, the co-founder of crypto hedge fund Three Arrows Capital,  now bankrupted, was arrested Friday afternoon at Changi Airport in Singapore. He had been trying to leave the country when he was detained, according to Teneo, which is overseeing the liquidation of the collapsed fund known as 3AC.

Source: https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/three-arrows-capital-co-founder-zhu-apprehended-singapore-2023-09-29/

Recently Circle has announced that it has deployed official USDC on two new Layer 2 networks, OP Mainnet and Base. This enables businesses to directly employ on/off-ramps for USDC within these networks, sidestepping Ethereum and likely experiencing reduced fees.

Currently, the native USDC supply totals nearly 25 million on OP Mainnet and approximately 19.8 million on Base.


With the addition of OP Mainnet and Base, $USDC is now natively issued on 11 blockchain networks
